    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.8.0-dev-nightly-471-gbb7853a62\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno, VIM - Vi IMproved 9.0 (2022 Jun 28, compiled Jul 26 2022 00:06:14) Included patches: 1-66\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nUbuntu 20.04.4(Windows 10 & WSL)\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nwezterm 20220408-101518-b908e2dd\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbuild from repo\r\n\r\n### How to reproduce the issue\r\n\r\n```vim\r\n\" minimal.vimrc\r\naugroup test\r\n  autocmd!\r\n  autocmd CmdlineLeave / echomsg getpos('.')\r\naugroup END\r\n```\r\n\r\n1. nvim --clean minimal.vimrc\r\n1. :source minimal.vimrc\\<CR>\r\n1. /END\\<CR>\r\n1. :messages\\<CR>\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n```\r\n[0, 1, 1, 0] (This is vim behavior)\r\n```\r\nor\r\n```\r\n[0, 4, 9, 0] (If it's the first word of the next hit, I can understand it)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n```\r\n[0, 4, 12, 0]\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Other\r\n\r\nrelated? https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/19500\r\n",
